	solutions and processes are usually developed by a group of people,
	working together. A grouping of people that share and create new
	knowledge can be considered as a Community of Practice (CoP). CoPs
	are places which provide a sound basis for organizational learning
	and encourage knowledge creation and acquisition. Virtual Communities
	of Practice (VCoPs) can perform a central role in promoting communication
	and collaboration between members who are dispersed in both time
	and space. Nevertheless, it is known that not all CoPs and VCoPs
