	Yet, while innovation may be facilitated within communities of practice,
	radical innovations frequently occur at the interstices across communities.
	Here, the performative advantages of communities of practice are
	less clear Moreover, while it has been suggested that managers play
	a critical role in constructing, aligning or supporting communities
